de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result

Class MetadataResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.MetadataResult
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FusionResult, ListResult

    public abstract class MetadataResult
extends java.lang.Object
    This abstract class is responsible for creating a result for the metadata query. It parses the metadata addicted to the given source with calling parseXMLMetadata(String) respectively parseVirtuosoMetadata(String) and adds the metadata to the metadataEntries list. Afterwards the RDF model is created and finally the String representation of the created model returned.
    The actual building of the model is done by the abstract createMetadataProperties() method which has to be implemented by the subclasess.
    Since:
    11.09.2013
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz
    See Also:
    parseXMLMetadata(String), parseVirtuosoMetadata(String), createRdfModel(), createMetadataProperties(), addDataProperty(ParsedMetadata), toRdfXml()

      • parseXMLMetadata

        public void parseXMLMetadata(java.lang.String uri)
                      throws MetadataNotFoundException,
                             ProcessingUriException
        This method is responsible for parsing the metadata from a XML file and adding it to the list of metadataEntries. Therefore it creates a new XMLMetadata object.
        Parameters:
        uri - - the corresponding metadata is searched for.
        Throws:
        MetadataNotFoundException - in case there was no metadata found in the XML file for this given URI.
        ProcessingUriException - in case there went something wrong while creating the XMLMetadata object.

      • parseVirtuosoMetadata

        public void parseVirtuosoMetadata(java.lang.String uri)
                           throws MetadataNotFoundException,
                                  ProcessingUriException
        This method is responsible for parsing the metadata from the virtuoso triple store and adding it to the list of metadataEntries. Therefore it creates a new VirtuosoMetadata object.
        Parameters:
        uri - - the corresponding metadata is searched for.
        Throws:
        MetadataNotFoundException - in case there was no metadata found in the XML file for this given URI.
        ProcessingUriException - in case there went something wrong while creating the VirtuosoMetadata object.
